description:
Cake Boss is an American reality television series that originally aired on the cable television network TLC. The series premiered on April 19, 2009, and spawned four spin-offs: Next Great Baker, Kitchen Boss, Bake You Rich, and Bakery Boss.

On January 26, 2015, Cake Boss was renewed for two additional seasons, which aired on TLC until 2017. Season 9 premiered on May 18, 2019, with the show moving to TLC's sister network, Discovery Family. The show officially ended on April 11, 2020.

description:
Breaking Bad is the groundbreaking series that gave us unforgettable characters like Walter White, Jesse Pinkman, Saul Goodman, Gus Fring, and iconic quotes like “I am the one who knocks.”
CREDITS: TM & © Sony Pictures Television (2025)
Cast: Bryan Cranston, Aaron Paul, Anna Gunn, Dean Norris, Giancarlo Esposito, Bob Odenkirk

Breaking Bad follows Walter White (Bryan Cranston), a high school chemistry teacher in New Mexico who, after a terminal cancer diagnosis, partners with former student Jesse Pinkman (Aaron Paul) to manufacture meth and secure his family’s future. As Walter transforms into the feared drug kingpin Heisenberg, he clashes with the cartel, the DEA, and enemies like Gus Fring, Mike Ehrmantraut, and even his own brother-in-law, Hank Schrader.

With dark humor, shocking twists, and quotes like “Say my name,” every episode delivers tension, transformation, and chaos. From Los Pollos Hermanos to the rise of Saul Goodman, Breaking Bad became one of the most acclaimed shows in TV history.
